edict the existence of strongly\nclustered populations at z~3, but with at least a factor of 10 lower number\ndensity than the one measured. The overall properties of this strongly\nclustered population consistently suggest that they are the progenitors, or\nbuilding blocks, of local massive early-type galaxies and z~1 EROs, close to\ntheir major epochs of formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Mar 2003 14:07:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
